BIB.AUTHOR: (J.H.DAVIES,L.YAFFE)
BIB.TITLE:
Nuclear Charge Dispersion in the High-Energy Fission
 of Uranium.
BIB.SAMPLE:
Uranium foil target, 47.5 mg/cm**2 thick, sandwiched
 between two similar foils to guard against recoil
 losses.
BIB.METHOD:
(ACTIV) Target irradiatiation usually of for the
 order of 30 minutes.
(CHSEP) Chemical separation procedure took about 40
 minutes.
BIB.CORRECTION_firstSub:
Small corrections for self-absorption in the 4 pi
 source.
BIB.ERR-ANALYS_firstSub:
(DATA-ERR) Errors quoted are standard deviations
 compounded from estimated errors in decay curve
 analyses, counter efficiencies, and chemical yield
 determinations.
BIB.ADD-RES:
Independent formation cross-sections of 135Cs and 137Cs
 have Been interpolated from charge dispersion curves
 and reported in Table 16.
BIB.CORRECTION:
136Cs contribution was subtracted from total gamma
 spectrum.
BIB.ERR-ANALYS:
Error of +-10% in accepted values of monitor cross
 sections was not included.
